  "title": "The Best Creator Posts About Pittsburgh Businesses",
  "subtitle": "TikToks made by Pittsburgh creators, ranked by plays. None of these came from the businesses themselves.",
  "angle": "the city is filming Pittsburgh businesses; the businesses are not posting back. Here's the proof, ranked.",
  "intro": "Page's Dairy Mart in Arlington pulled 62,800 plays on a single TikTok this quarter. It was filmed by @bhphotographypa. Page's didn't make that video, didn't pay for it, and has no TikTok account to redirect the people who watched it. That's the cleanest version of this story. The rest of this list tells variations on the same one.\n\nTwenty-eight creator-made TikToks. Seventeen Pittsburgh businesses. 171,521 plays. Not one of those videos came from the business it filmed. @lattebrothers pulled 10,700 plays to Margaux in East Liberty while inviting other Pittsburgh shops to DM them for a visit. @briannaquirke_ put Pusadee's Garden in front of thousands of viewers with a caption that reads like a personal recommendation from a friend, because it is. The businesses are receiving the attention. They are not starting it.\n\nThis is Pittsburgh being filmed by its residents while its small businesses watch from the sideline. Issue 02 will ask why more of them aren't picking up the camera themselves.",
